verses.text_plain: Woe unto them that decree unrighteous decrees, and that write grievousness which they have prescribed;
verses.verse_html:
1Woe unto them that decree unrighteous decrees, and that write grievousness which they have prescribed; ▼
▼ that write…: or, to the writers that write grievousness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that write…: or, to the writers that write grievousness
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that write…: or, to the writers that write grievousness

verses.text_plain: To turn aside the needy from judgment, and to take away the right from the poor of my people, that widows may be their prey, and that they may rob the fatherless!
verses.verse_html: 2To turn aside the needy from judgment, and to take away the right from the poor of my people, that widows may be their prey, and that they may rob the fatherless!

verses.text_plain: And what will ye do in the day of visitation, and in the desolation which shall come from far? to whom will ye flee for help? and where will ye leave your glory?
verses.verse_html: 3And what will ye do in the day of visitation, and in the desolation which shall come from far? to whom will ye flee for help? and where will ye leave your glory?

verses.text_plain: Without me they shall bow down under the prisoners, and they shall fall under the slain. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.
verses.verse_html: 4Without me they shall bow down under the prisoners, and they shall fall under the slain. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.

verses.text_plain: O Assyrian, the rod of mine anger, and the staff in their hand is mine indignation.
verses.verse_html:
5O Assyrian, the rod of mine anger, and the staff in their hand is mine indignation. ▼
▼ O…: or, Woe to the Assyrian: Heb. Asshur
 , ▼
▼ and: or, though

footnotes.body_text: ▼ O…: or, Woe to the Assyrian: Heb. Asshur
footnotes.body_html: ▼ O…: or, Woe to the Assyrian: Heb. Asshur

verses.text_plain: I will send him against an hypocritical nation, and against the people of my wrath will I give him a charge, to take the spoil, and to take the prey, and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.
verses.verse_html:
6I will send him against an hypocritical nation, and against the people of my wrath will I give him a charge, to take the spoil, and to take the prey, and to tread them down like the mire of the streets. ▼
▼ tread…: Heb. lay them a treading

tokens.text: will I give him a charge

footnotes.body_text: ▼ tread…: Heb. lay them a treading
footnotes.body_html: ▼ tread…: Heb. lay them a treading

verses.text_plain: Howbeit he meaneth not so, neither doth his heart think so; but it is in his heart to destroy and cut off nations not a few.
verses.verse_html: 7Howbeit he meaneth not so, neither doth his heart think so; but it is in his heart to destroy and cut off nations not a few.

tokens.text: not so, neither doth his heart

verses.text_plain: For he saith, Are not my princes altogether kings?
verses.verse_html: 8For he saith, Are not my princes altogether kings?

verses.text_plain: Is not Calno as Carchemish? is not Hamath as Arpad? is not Samaria as Damascus?
verses.verse_html: 9Is not Calno as Carchemish? is not Hamath as Arpad? is not Samaria as Damascus?

verses.text_plain: As my hand hath found the kingdoms of the idols, and whose graven images did excel them of Jerusalem and of Samaria;
verses.verse_html: 10As my hand hath found the kingdoms of the idols, and whose graven images did excel them of Jerusalem and of Samaria;

verses.text_plain: Shall I not, as I have done unto Samaria and her idols, so do to Jerusalem and her idols?
verses.verse_html: 11Shall I not, as I have done unto Samaria and her idols, so do to Jerusalem and her idols?

tokens.text: Shall I not, as I have done

verses.text_plain: Wherefore it shall come to pass, that when the Lord hath performed his whole work upon mount Zion and on Jerusalem, I will punish the fruit of the stout heart of the king of Assyria, and the glory of his high looks.
verses.verse_html:
12Wherefore it shall come to pass, that when the Lord hath performed his whole work upon mount Zion and on Jerusalem, I will punish the fruit of the stout heart of the king of Assyria, and the glory of his high looks. ▼
▼ punish: Heb. visit upon
 , ▼
▼ stout…: Heb. greatness of the heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ punish: Heb. visit upon

footnotes.body_text: ▼ stout…: Heb. greatness of the heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ stout…: Heb. greatness of the heart

verses.text_plain: For he saith, By the strength of my hand I have done it, and by my wisdom; for I am prudent: and I have removed the bounds of the people, and have robbed their treasures, and I have put down the inhabitants like a valiant man:
verses.verse_html:
13For he saith, By the strength of my hand I have done it, and by my wisdom; for I am prudent: and I have removed the bounds of the people, and have robbed their treasures, and I have put down the inhabitants like a valiant man: ▼
▼ a valiant…: or, many people

footnotes.body_html: ▼ a valiant…: or, many people

verses.text_plain: And my hand hath found as a nest the riches of the people: and as one gathereth eggs that are left, have I gathered all the earth; and there was none that moved the wing, or opened the mouth, or peeped.
verses.verse_html: 14And my hand hath found as a nest the riches of the people: and as one gathereth eggs that are left, have I gathered all the earth; and there was none that moved the wing, or opened the mouth, or peeped.

tokens.text: and there was none that moved

verses.text_plain: Shall the axe boast itself against him that heweth therewith? or shall the saw magnify itself against him that shaketh it? as if the rod should shake itself against them that lift it up, or as if the staff should lift up itself, as if it were no wood.
verses.verse_html:
15Shall the axe boast itself against him that heweth therewith? or shall the saw magnify itself against him that shaketh it? as if the rod should shake itself against them that lift it up, or as if the staff should lift up itself, as if it were no wood. ▼
▼ the rod…: or, a rod should shake them that lift it up
 , ▼
▼ itself, as if…: or, that which is not wood

tokens.text: against them that lift it up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the rod…: or, a rod should shake them that lift it up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the rod…: or, a rod should shake them that lift it up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ itself, as if…: or, that which is not wood
footnotes.body_html: ▼ itself, as if…: or, that which is not wood

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall the Lord, the Lord of hosts, send among his fat ones leanness; and under his glory he shall kindle a burning like the burning of a fire.
verses.verse_html: 16Therefore shall the Lord, the Lord of hosts, send among his fat ones leanness; and under his glory he shall kindle a burning like the burning of a fire.

tokens.text: like the burning of a fire

verses.text_plain: And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his Holy One for a flame: and it shall burn and devour his thorns and his briers in one day;
verses.verse_html: 17And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his Holy One for a flame: and it shall burn and devour his thorns and his briers in one day;

verses.text_plain: And shall consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field, both soul and body: and they shall be as when a standardbearer fainteth.
verses.verse_html:
18And shall consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field, both soul and body: and they shall be as when a standardbearer fainteth. ▼
▼ both…: Heb. from the soul, and even to the flesh

tokens.text: and they shall be as when a standardbearer

footnotes.body_text: ▼ both…: Heb. from the soul, and even to the flesh
footnotes.body_html: ▼ both…: Heb. from the soul, and even to the flesh

verses.text_plain: And the rest of the trees of his forest shall be few, that a child may write them.
verses.verse_html:
19And the rest of the trees of his forest shall be few, that a child may write them. ▼
▼ few: Heb. number

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, that the remnant of Israel, and such as are escaped of the house of Jacob, shall no more again stay upon him that smote them; but shall stay upon the Lord, the Holy One of Israel, in truth.
verses.verse_html: 20And it shall come to pass in that day, that the remnant of Israel, and such as are escaped of the house of Jacob, shall no more again stay upon him that smote them; but shall stay upon the Lord, the Holy One of Israel, in truth.

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day

verses.text_plain: The remnant shall return, even the remnant of Jacob, unto the mighty God.
verses.verse_html: 21The remnant shall return, even the remnant of Jacob, unto the mighty God.

verses.text_plain: For though thy people Israel be as the sand of the sea, yet a remnant of them shall return: the consumption decreed shall overflow with righteousness.
verses.verse_html:
22For though thy people Israel be as the sand of the sea, yet a remnant of them shall return: the consumption decreed shall overflow with righteousness. ▼
▼ of them: Heb. in, or, among, etc
 , ▼
▼ with: or, in

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of them: Heb. in, or, among, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of them: Heb. in, or, among, etc

verses.text_plain: For the Lord God of hosts shall make a consumption, even determined, in the midst of all the land.
verses.verse_html: 23For the Lord God of hosts shall make a consumption, even determined, in the midst of all the land.

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God of hosts, O my people that dwellest in Zion, be not afraid of the Assyrian: he shall smite thee with a rod, and shall lift up his staff against thee, after the manner of Egypt.
verses.verse_html:
24Therefore thus saith the Lord God of hosts, O my people that dwellest in Zion, be not afraid of the Assyrian: he shall smite thee with a rod, and shall lift up his staff against thee, after the manner of Egypt. ▼
▼ and shall…: or, but he shall lift up his staff for

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and shall…: or, but he shall lift up his staff for
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and shall…: or, but he shall lift up his staff for

verses.text_plain: For yet a very little while, and the indignation shall cease, and mine anger in their destruction.
verses.verse_html: 25For yet a very little while, and the indignation shall cease, and mine anger in their destruction.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord of hosts shall stir up a scourge for him according to the slaughter of Midian at the rock of Oreb: and as his rod was upon the sea, so shall he lift it up after the manner of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 26And the Lord of hosts shall stir up a scourge for him according to the slaughter of Midian at the rock of Oreb: and as his rod was upon the sea, so shall he lift it up after the manner of Egypt.

tokens.text: for him according to the slaughter
so shall he lift it up

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, that his burden shall be taken away from off thy shoulder, and his yoke from off thy neck, and the yoke shall be destroyed because of the anointing.
verses.verse_html:
27And it shall come to pass in that day, that his burden shall be taken away from off thy shoulder, and his yoke from off thy neck, and the yoke shall be destroyed because of the anointing. ▼
▼ be taken…: Heb. remove

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day

footnotes.body_html: ▼ be taken…: Heb. remove

verses.text_plain: He is come to Aiath, he is passed to Migron; at Michmash he hath laid up his carriages:
verses.verse_html: 28He is come to Aiath, he is passed to Migron; at Michmash he hath laid up his carriages:

verses.text_plain: They are gone over the passage: they have taken up their lodging at Geba; Ramah is afraid; Gibeah of Saul is fled.
verses.verse_html: 29They are gone over the passage: they have taken up their lodging at Geba; Ramah is afraid; Gibeah of Saul is fled.

tokens.text: they have taken up their lodging

verses.text_plain: Lift up thy voice, O daughter of Gallim: cause it to be heard unto Laish, O poor Anathoth.
verses.verse_html:
30Lift up thy voice, O daughter of Gallim: cause it to be heard unto Laish, O poor Anathoth. ▼
▼ Lift…: Heb. Cry shrill with

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Lift…: Heb. Cry shrill with

verses.text_plain: Madmenah is removed; the inhabitants of Gebim gather themselves to flee.
verses.verse_html: 31Madmenah is removed; the inhabitants of Gebim gather themselves to flee.

verses.text_plain: As yet shall he remain at Nob that day: he shall shake his hand against the mount of the daughter of Zion, the hill of Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 32As yet shall he remain at Nob that day: he shall shake his hand against the mount of the daughter of Zion, the hill of Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: Behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts, shall lop the bough with terror: and the high ones of stature shall be hewn down, and the haughty shall be humbled.
verses.verse_html: 33Behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts, shall lop the bough with terror: and the high ones of stature shall be hewn down, and the haughty shall be humbled.

verses.text_plain: And he shall cut down the thickets of the forest with iron, and Lebanon shall fall by a mighty one.
verses.verse_html:
34And he shall cut down the thickets of the forest with iron, and Lebanon shall fall by a mighty one. ▼
▼ by…: or, mightily
